				<li id="16764521" class="cmnt-root" data="4" data-d="1661747156000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578449/Black-Flame-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">29 Aug 2022 00:25</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16764521" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I&apos;ve found this to be a great go-to against very high health bosses/enemies. Between the enemy health% damage which ignores resistances and its low FP cost, it gives you a considerable boost in situations where your swings aren&apos;t doing very large amounts of damage to the boss. This comes up during a few bosses in NG (Fire Giant and Elden Beast), but this is also very helpful for either NG+ or challenge runs (the very low faith requirement might also apply here), where your dps might otherwise be struggling against many bosses. The other blackflame incantations run into the problem of being slow and dodgeable against more agile opponents, as well as hogging more of your FP.<br/><br/>Also, and I cannot overstate this, it looks very cool, and the fact you can apply it while leaping at your opponent is just the best.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16764521" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16764521" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-