				<li id="16733112" class="cmnt-root" data="7" data-d="1657338471000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578449/Black-Flame-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">08 Jul 2022 23:47</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16733112" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Probably the most reliable DOT effectagainst bosses, however really hard to use properly. It is obviously better than poison, which deals an enormous 4% of target boss hp over 30 seconds (sarcasm), in theory dealing the same damage 7 times faster. It has to be recasted, that is a downside, but the cast is pretty fast on itself, even without Radagon&apos;s or huge investments in Dex. Blackflame is in general less effective than Scarlet Rot, but there are bosses with huge healthpools that are immune to being rot; mostly Elden Beast and Malenia. Also, to inflict red plague you have to build it up by hitting either with dedicated weapons or with arrows, both being extremely easy to dodge by agiles like Maliketh or hell, even Morgott. But everything up till this point is overshadowed by a single statement here, that may cause heavy arguing: it has the best looking cast animation out of every single buff in the entire series</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16733112" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collaps