				<li id="16699097" class="cmnt-root" data="1" data-d="1653875092000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578449/Black-Flame-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">29 May 2022 21:44</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16699097" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Niche incantation. It won&apos;t work very well if you don&apos;t have the patience to reapply it and/or like using a big bonk weapon, but it really shines in conjunction with faster weapons. I run a hybrid dex/faith build and this thing alongside the godskin stitcher SLAPS. I can often land three hits in quick succession, sometimes even more, and it just melts bosses.<br/><br/>Pros: Low FP cost, grows in effectiveness the more HP the enemy has (especially useful against runebears, I can kill them twice as fast as usual with this).<br/><br/>Cons: You have to reapply often, which means if you don&apos;t fight alongside spirits you&apos;ll need to be careful with it. Constant recasts mean you&apos;ll run out of FP quickly if you alternate between incantations (which I don&apos;t recommend).</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16699097" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16699097" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span cl