				<li id="16669961" class="cmnt-root" data="-2" data-d="1651781573000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578449/Black-Flame-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">05 May 2022 16:12</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16669961" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">If it’s supposed to be a Drawstring equivalent of a Spell Buff then at least make it stronger than the other Spell buffs. Constantly rebuffing, the FP cost, the fact that in buffing you miss times to actually attack. It needs at the very least be 10-12 seconds to be useful mid fight and it would make sacrificing a Ring slot for Old Lord’s actually worth it. <br/><br/>As it stands, you need Old Lord’s to make it functional but even then, since for whatever reason Godslayer Seal doesn’t enhance this Spell, you are still hitting lower than any of the other Spell buffs. Yes, the DoT on large health bars are its selling point but what about literally everything else? <br/><br/>Hones Just give it a duration buff that’s all it needs. Or. You know. Just give us Catch Black Flame and make Black Flame Blade completely obsolete.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16669961" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16669961" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-shar