				<li id="16669623" class="cmnt-root" data="78" data-d="1651779346000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578449/Black-Flame-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">05 May 2022 15:35</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16669623" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Okay, so hear me out (but also TL:DR at the bottom):<br/><br/>First off, the blackflame debuff IS refreshed every time you apply it to an enemy (this can be easily confirmed by hitting any enemy, waiting a moment, and then hitting them again - the duration is extended to the full 2 seconds after each hit).<br/><br/>Now, with that in mind, this debuff is most effective when it&apos;s reapplied within two seconds of each application, thus keeping the blackflame debuff ticking on an enemy. Using this buff on a fast weapon makes this easier to achieve but isn&apos;t absolutely necessary. Every second that this debuff is active, you burn the enemy for 1% of their max health with unmitigable damage. I&apos;ll say that again because it&apos;s important, EACH SECOND THIS IS ACTIVE IT BURNS THE ENEMY FOR 1% OF THEIR MAX HEALTH WITH UNMITIGABLE DAMAGE.<br/><br/>So, assuming that you keep this ticking for its full duration you&apos;re looking at 7% of the enemy&apos;s max health burned per application, which is really good in the later NG+ cycles when enemies&apos; health pools are obscenely large. That being said, the closer to the end of the buff&apos;s duration you hit the longer it&apos;s extended. If you managed to hit the enemy on the seventh (or so) second that the buff was active you&apos;d refresh the debuff for an additional two seconds, thus dealing 9% of the enemy&apos;s max health total. This spell&apos;s starting to sound pretty good.<br/><br/>But, it can be even better. With the Old Lord&apos;s talisman (increases duration of buffs by +30%) we increase that 7 second duration to around 9 seconds, which means that if you&apos;re able to keep the buff active the entire duration AND manage to land a hit within the last few moments of the buff you&apos;re looking at a whopping 11% of the enemy&apos;s max health burned for 15 FP.<br/><br/>Now, how to do that consistently: Whenever you&apos;re looking to buff, treat the window like a light attack with a regular-sized weapon (think a straight sword or katana) - you&apos;re looking for a slightly heavier attack, but not necessarily one that puts the boss into a long recovery animation (you can also use the Radagon Icon talisman to make the timing easier). Apply this buff while doing any other action: sprinting, jumping, fastbuff, or - my personal favorite - rolling. Do NOT cast it standing normally, this takes significantly (maybe 50%?) more time to buff than chaining it with an action. After buffing, just aim to hit at least once every two seconds to maintain the buff - rolling light attacks are your friends here.<br/><br/>Also, take note that this buff IS applied to enemies hit by the weapon skill of your buffed weapon, but there&apos;s another post detailing that so read that one for more information!<br/><br/>What that post doesn&apos;t mention though is that this is applied to a pulley crossbow in the offhand, similar to bloodflame blade. The timing on this wastes a lot of the buff since you have to swap off the talisman that you used to cast it with but it gives you a safe alternative to applying this buff to bosses that may have tougher melee timings, longer times before you can counterattack, or will just flat murder you if you get too close. (Note that the pulley crossbow interaction doesn&apos;t carry over into any other offhanded armament that I&apos;ve tested or heard of so it might get patched out. The ashes of war application should be intentional though.)<br/><br/>The faith scaling on this is practically pointless for a 7-second buff considering the mana cost, just use electrify armament instead. Since the faith scaling is worthless, this spell works best at 17 faith.<br/><br/>I haven&apos;t tried it in PvP but it doesn&apos;t really seem like it&apos;d be that good - 11% over 11 seconds of constantly refreshing the debuff is super low, even against someone with the max health of around 3k that&apos;s only an additional 330 damage (plus the so-so fire damage but whatever.)<br/><br/>Also note that this does have a SHORT duration and so you need to constantly reapply it. This spell WILL eat through your FP bar pretty fast, but investing a few points into mind helps combat this. I mean, technically speaking you&apos;ll only need a max of 10 casts to kill ANYTHING that doesn&apos;t heal as long as you keep the blackflame debuff applied so...<br/><br/>This is probably my favorite spell in the game and once you get the hang of how it works it just feels amazing. I like to swap between this and bloodflame blade applied to a keen Nagakiba (Pulley Crossbow offhand :P ) based on if the enemy can be bled or not and the amount of percentage-based damage you do is ridiculous.<br/><br/>TL:DR - Burns about 9% of your enemy&apos;s max HP per cast (11% with Old Lord&apos;s talisman) if you keep it active for the full duration. Fastbuff using rolls or certain ashes of war, don&apos;t cast it standing. If you don&apos;t want to get close to the enemy you can use pulley crossbow with this like you would bloodflame blade. Use it in PvE but not PvP. Best at 17 faith.<br/><br/>Hope this helps people understand the spell a bit more!</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16669623" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16669623" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">3</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>84</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>6</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16669623"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16669623" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16669623"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
