				<li id="16661911" class="cmnt-root" data="15" data-d="1651351682000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578449/Black-Flame-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">30 Apr 2022 16:48</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16661911" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">It&apos;s not even that bad, with the godslayer seal and appropriate talismans it adds a very significant amount of damage, works on nearly every foe, the percentage-based effect is really good if you use it against bosses, pairs very well with fast weapons despite not stacking, the duration is not too short to deal more damage with it than several casts of black flame, especially if you use a shortsword or something like that, can be paired with old lord&apos;s talisman for extra efficiency, but there is one thing about it that makes it inferior to other weapon buffs in the long run. To me, it&apos;s not even its duration, after using it for some time you get used to the way it is applied, and, spoiler, it is fast, especially after dodging or attacking, which creates a very fun and dynamic rythm, especially if you are fighting agressive bosses. Right now I am fighting Malenia, and though I am very far from being actually good at the game, I can tell that using this incant even against such bosses is very much possible. So, the main reason I just can&apos;t recommend using it in its current state, unless you are, like me, completely mesmerized by the beauty of the black flame effect and enjoy the way applying this feels, because this incantation right now is just inferior to other weapon enchantments is the... FP cost. Yeah, 15 is kind of too much for what it does and really too much for how often you will reapply this if you want to use this as your primary source of damage. I, while definitely not a game developer, would suggest decreasing the FP cost to 10 or even 8 to make this thing more viable as an incantation to use constantly, a reliable working horse against bosses and large enemies. And yes, I do intend to still use it against Malenia instead of things like electrify (which sounds good considering the fact that she stands in a puddle half the time), because I am a pervert and proud of it. Thanks for reading this unreasonably long rant about an objectively mediocre spell and take care.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16661911" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16661911" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">3</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>21</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>6</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16661911"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16661911" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16661911"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
